Nigeria on Monday recorded 216 new cases of coronavirus (COVID-19). The Nigeria Center for Disease Control, NCDC, confirmed this on its Twitter page. With this development, the total number of COVID-19 cases in Nigeria has risen to 6175. The tweet read: “216 new cases of #COVID19; 74-Lagos, 34-Katsina, 19-Oyo, 17-Kano,13-Edo, 10-Zamfara,8-Ogun,8-Gombe,8-Borno, 7-Bauchi 7-Kwara, 4-FCT, 3-Kaduna, 3-Enugu, 2-Rivers “6175 cases of #COVID19 in Nigeria, Discharged: 1644, Deaths: 191.” Meanwhile, President Muhammadu Buhari has extended the gradual easing of the lockdown in Lagos, Abuja and Ogun States by another two weeks. NCDC announces 381 fresh cases of COVID-19 Coronavirus: NCDC list States with COVID-19 cases, number of infected persons NCDC confirms 146 new cases of coronavirus